<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B4504022002" page = "1">
<title>
Circuit Description
</title>
<ptxt>
When the ignition is set “ON”, power is supplied to ABS control module. Then power is supplied to pump motor and solenoid valve in other line by the switching function in ABS control module.
</ptxt>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B4504022003">
<title>
Troubleshooting
</title>
<diag type = "test" id = "AENAP70B4504022004">
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B4504022005">
<title>
Fuse check
</title>
<question>
Are “ABS MOT” fuse, “ABS SOL” fuse and “ABS<sup>”</sup> fuse in good condition?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 2.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace fuse and check for short circuit to ground.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B4504022006">
<title>
Ignition power supply circuit check 
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Confirm that ignition is “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect “E24” connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check for proper terminal connection to “E24” connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
If connections are OK, set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Measure voltage between “E24-3” terminal and ground.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is it 10 – 14 V?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 3.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace “B1” circuit.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B4504022007">
<title>
Pump motor and solenoid valve power supply circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Confirm that ignition is “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Measure voltage between each of “E24-26” and “E24-13” terminals and ground.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Are they 10 – 14 V?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 4.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace “A1” circuit and/or “A2” circuit.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B4504022008">
<title>
ABS control module ground circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Measure resistance between each of “E24-14” and “E24-27” terminals and ground.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is resistance less than 2 &#937;?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
ABS control module power supply and ground circuits are in good condition.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace “C1” circuit and/or “C2” circuit.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
</diag>
